<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0031" RecordId="021-000002439"><Name>Delia (Accademia)</Name><AlternativeName>Accademia dei Deli</AlternativeName><City CityId="3"><CityItalianName>Padova</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Padua</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Patavii</CityLatinName></City><EmblemDescription>The island of Delos</EmblemDescription><Motto>Nunc demum immota</Motto><StartDate>1608</StartDate><EndDate>1801</EndDate><DateText>1608-1801</DateText><Notes>A list of names of academicians is in Valeriano Bonvicini, Matematiche discipline (1666), and Maylender, II, pp. 162-3. For a history of the Academy, see Giorgio Orefice, `L`Accademia Delia di Padova`, in Atti e memorie dell`Accademia patavina di lettere scienze ed arti (1965-66), pp. 238-94. Unpublished manuscript documents appear in antonio favaro, Galileo Galilei e lo studio di Padova 2 voll. (Padua 1966). One publication related to the Academy, but not in British Library collections, is: Oratione del povero Academico Delio [Antonio Frigimelica], da lui recitata nell`Academia, in morte del sig. Gio. Francesco Mussato, con alcune compositioni latine di diuersi nel medesimo soggetto In Padova: appresso Pietro Paolo Tozzi (Patavii: typis Laurentij Pasquati, impressoris cameralis, 1614). The Accademia Delia was preceded by Academia degli Oplosofisti, which was mentioned in Malatesta Massari, Compendio dell`heroica arte di cavalleria (Padua, 1600), p. 44v; Camilli, Imprese illustri, part II (Venice, 1586), pp. 3, 4, 5; Ferro, Teatro d`imprese, part II, p. 486. </Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="15184" RecordId="022-000001226"><Name>Sagredo,Nicol&#242;,Cavalier Procuratore di San Marco,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="9146" RecordId="022-000001609"><Name>Papafava dei Carraresi,Marsilio,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="15882" RecordId="022-000002443"><Name>Conti,Annibale,Count,</Name><Nick